WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.676 --> 00:00:11.803
["Sing. Sing. Sing" playing]

2
00:01:14.157 --> 00:01:16.284
- [music stops]
- [cheering]

3
00:01:30.256 --> 00:01:31.257
Judy Hale.

4
00:01:31.883 --> 00:01:32.884
That's the artist.

5
00:01:33.009 --> 00:01:35.386
Sorry. I'm new here.
so I still need the thingy.

6
00:01:35.470 --> 00:01:37.806
[chuckles] So how much
would a Judy Hale set me back?

7
00:01:38.264 --> 00:01:42.310
Well. between nine and twenty thousand.
depending on the size.

8
00:01:42.977 --> 00:01:43.853
Nine and...

9
00:01:44.437 --> 00:01:45.605
- Jesus!
- Ooh!

10
00:01:45.688 --> 00:01:48.358
Looks like these are all sold.
I guess she's famous or something.

11
00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:49.776
Yeah. I've heard of her.

12
00:01:50.151 --> 00:01:53.780
Hey. so what can you tell me about the '66
Mustang that's usually parked out front?

13
00:01:53.947 --> 00:01:55.115
Oh. I don't know.

14
00:01:55.490 --> 00:01:57.283
Actually. let me go ask my boss.

15
00:01:57.367 --> 00:01:58.284
Cool. Thank you.

16
00:02:00.578 --> 00:02:01.538
[sighs]

17
00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:05.208
[Steve speaking Greek]

18
00:02:06.126 --> 00:02:06.960
- Hey there.
- Hey.

19
00:02:07.043 --> 00:02:08.919
- Hey. Steve Wood.
- Steve?

20
00:02:09.253 --> 00:02:12.799
- Yeah. And you are?
- Dying to know if your Mustang's for sale.

21
00:02:14.884 --> 00:02:17.053
- Sorry. What did you say your name was?
- I didn't.

22
00:02:18.096 --> 00:02:19.973
You know.
I drive by this gallery all the time.

23
00:02:20.223 --> 00:02:22.892
- It doesn't seem like you're ever open.
- It's gallery hours.

24
00:02:23.309 --> 00:02:25.145
- It's a thing. It's a real thing.
- Hmm.

25
00:02:25.979 --> 00:02:28.356
Right. So. the Mustang. Where is it?

26
00:02:28.481 --> 00:02:31.317
Sorry. I'm not gonna be able to help you
with that one. broseph. Uh...

27
00:02:31.401 --> 00:02:33.444
- Maybe it belongs to one of my artists.
- Oh. yeah?

28
00:02:33.653 --> 00:02:35.155
Yeah. Probably definitely.

29
00:02:35.238 --> 00:02:36.781
Probably definitely Judy Hale?

30
00:02:39.492 --> 00:02:40.326
Uh...

31
00:02:42.620 --> 00:02:45.039
No. I mean. I don't know. I'm not sure.

32
00:02:45.665 --> 00:02:47.292
Why don't you call me if you get sure?

33
00:02:47.792 --> 00:02:49.002
All right. Will do...

34
00:02:50.962 --> 00:02:51.963
Detective.

35
00:02:53.423 --> 00:02:54.257
[door closes]

36
00:02:56.384 --> 00:02:57.635
Judy. your breakfast is ready.

37
00:02:58.469 --> 00:02:59.387
I made it myself.

38
00:02:59.929 --> 00:03:03.057
Oh! Look at you. That is so sweet.

39
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:06.394
Yeah. It's pancakes.
They're vegan... mostly.

40
00:03:07.103 --> 00:03:08.771
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

41
00:03:08.938 --> 00:03:09.939
[Jen chuckles]

42
00:03:10.064 --> 00:03:10.899
I wouldn't eat that.

43
00:03:11.274 --> 00:03:12.442
- No.
- Seriously?

44
00:03:12.984 --> 00:03:14.986
- It's the thought.
- It is the thought.

45
00:03:16.237 --> 00:03:17.614
How was your dance class?

46
00:03:17.780 --> 00:03:19.115
Oh! It was amazing.

47
00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:23.369
I'm sore as shit right now.
but thank you for making me do that.

48
00:03:24.287 --> 00:03:25.246
How are you doing?

49
00:03:26.372 --> 00:03:29.125
- I'm doing a little better.
- Okay.

50
00:03:31.669 --> 00:03:32.503
No. you're not.

51
00:03:32.587 --> 00:03:35.215
- No. I'm not. I'm sorry.
- Oh. honey. honey.

52
00:03:35.298 --> 00:03:36.174
[Judy sobs]

53
00:03:36.424 --> 00:03:37.634
It's just hard.

54
00:03:38.927 --> 00:03:42.680
I'm trying to process the idea
that I'm never gonna have children.

55
00:03:43.640 --> 00:03:45.725
- You know. you can always adopt.
- [scoffs]

56
00:03:46.601 --> 00:03:49.229
Yeah. I'm 41 and homeless.
send me all your children.

57
00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:50.980
I wouldn't... open with that.

58
00:03:54.275 --> 00:03:56.736
[sniffs] All I ever wanted
was to have a family.

59
00:03:58.780 --> 00:04:00.240
You... you have us.

60
00:04:01.157 --> 00:04:02.659
You're a part of this family.

61
00:04:04.744 --> 00:04:06.287
- Really?
- Yeah.

62
00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:12.377
- Thank you.
- Oh. gosh.

63
00:04:12.460 --> 00:04:14.128
That was supposed
to make you feel better.

64
00:04:14.212 --> 00:04:15.505
[sobbing] It does.

65
00:04:15.588 --> 00:04:18.382
Mom. I need a new laptop.
Mine's getting old.

66
00:04:18.466 --> 00:04:20.593
Not now. Charlie. Judy's having a moment.

67
00:04:20.677 --> 00:04:22.053
What. so my needs come last?

68
00:04:22.512 --> 00:04:24.597
Do you know how much a new laptop costs?

69
00:04:25.056 --> 00:04:26.808
I can't even swing
the mortgage this month.

70
00:04:26.891 --> 00:04:29.227
So your laptop is a little low on my list.

71
00:04:30.979 --> 00:04:32.897
- Oh. boy.
- [Judy] Wait. what?

72
00:04:33.147 --> 00:04:34.565
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah.

73
00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:36.317
It's just money's a little tight.

74
00:04:37.110 --> 00:04:39.445
- It's very tight.
- Let me contribute.

75
00:04:40.113 --> 00:04:41.030
No.

76
00:04:41.447 --> 00:04:43.241
Can you pay a mortgage with a debit card?

77
00:04:43.574 --> 00:04:45.576
I still have the one
that I shared with Steve.

78
00:04:45.910 --> 00:04:46.911
- You do?
- Yeah.

79
00:04:47.161 --> 00:04:50.456
He has so much money. I never touch it
myself. but he wouldn't miss it.

80
00:04:50.540 --> 00:04:53.334
No. You know. I don't need Steve Wood
paying for my mortgage.

81
00:04:53.418 --> 00:04:54.919
Does Steve wanna buy me a new laptop?

82
00:04:55.003 --> 00:04:57.171
If you want a new laptop. go get a job!

83
00:04:57.255 --> 00:04:59.674
Did Henry need to get a job
to pay for his stupid fucking choir?

84
00:04:59.757 --> 00:05:03.469
[laughs] Yeah. You wanna join the fucking
church choir. sure. I'll pay to see that.

85
00:05:03.553 --> 00:05:05.096
I'd rather get hit by a car.

86
00:05:07.598 --> 00:05:09.309
- You watch your mouth!
- Too late.

87
00:05:09.392 --> 00:05:11.936
Don't you dare disrespect
your father like that ever again!

88
00:05:12.020 --> 00:05:13.855
Me disrespect him?
You are one to fucking talk!

89
00:05:13.938 --> 00:05:14.772
Go to your room!

90
00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:17.358
I'm gonna call Grandma.
because at least she gives a shit.

91
00:05:17.442 --> 00:05:20.820
You know what? You can't go running
to Lorna every time you need something!

92
00:05:21.321 --> 00:05:24.407
Lorna. no one sells like me.
You know that.

93
00:05:24.907 --> 00:05:27.493
I would be a huge asset to this team.

94
00:05:27.785 --> 00:05:29.537
So. you need me.

95
00:05:29.912 --> 00:05:32.081
As much as it pains me
to admit that. yes. I do.

96
00:05:32.915 --> 00:05:35.376
My income has been... really stalled.

97
00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:37.337
Because your business partner dumped you.

98
00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:39.922
- Don't.
- Because you're a real estate pariah.

99
00:05:40.006 --> 00:05:41.674
Oh. Jesus Christ. Lorna!

100
00:05:42.008 --> 00:05:43.843
Isn't it exhausting hating me this much?

101
00:05:44.302 --> 00:05:46.220
- I don't hate you.
- Thank you.

102
00:05:46.304 --> 00:05:48.765
- I'm just consistently disappointed.
- There it is.

103
00:05:48.848 --> 00:05:51.726
You may pretend not to remember.
Jennifer. but I do.

104
00:05:52.685 --> 00:05:56.147
One day. you were my protégé
and then you deserted me.

105
00:05:56.230 --> 00:05:59.734
tempted by whatever fruits
Christopher dangled in your face.

106
00:05:59.817 --> 00:06:02.111
No. I don't think
that's an apt metaphor in this...

107
00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:04.989
Do you have any idea
how it feels to be abandoned?

108
00:06:07.575 --> 00:06:08.659
Yes. I do.

109
00:06:10.328 --> 00:06:12.038
But this job isn't for me. Lorna.

110
00:06:12.747 --> 00:06:13.664
It's for the boys.

111
00:06:14.374 --> 00:06:17.919
They are craving
stability and electronics.

112
00:06:18.669 --> 00:06:21.506
Just please... help me give that to them.

113
00:06:25.802 --> 00:06:26.761
Well played.

114
00:06:27.720 --> 00:06:29.389
You know they're all I have left.

115
00:06:30.765 --> 00:06:32.141
And I let them down.

116
00:06:33.559 --> 00:06:34.727
What are you talking about?

117
00:06:38.815 --> 00:06:40.149
The night Ted died.

118
00:06:41.275 --> 00:06:42.235
he called me.

119
00:06:47.448 --> 00:06:50.368
Yeah. you've. um... you've mentioned that.

120
00:06:50.451 --> 00:06:53.287
[faint heartbeat]

121
00:06:53.371 --> 00:06:54.997
I can't stop thinking about it.

122
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:00.628
I didn't answer.

123
00:07:00.711 --> 00:07:01.754
[heartbeat fading]

124
00:07:01.838 --> 00:07:05.508
He didn't leave a message.
but I know he needed me.

125
00:07:06.634 --> 00:07:07.760
A mother knows.

126
00:07:08.386 --> 00:07:10.179
And... I wasn't there.

127
00:07:11.722 --> 00:07:12.682
Where were you?

128
00:07:16.644 --> 00:07:17.854
I may have...

129
00:07:19.605 --> 00:07:21.816
taken a powerful sleeping aid.

130
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:26.612
Okay. Look. Lorna.
don't beat yourself up about that.

131
00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:28.406
It's not your fault that Ted died.

132
00:07:28.489 --> 00:07:29.824
- Isn't it?
- No.

133
00:07:29.907 --> 00:07:34.328
If a butterfly flaps its wings in Japan.
doesn't it cause a hurricane in Florida?

134
00:07:34.412 --> 00:07:36.747
I honestly don't know
what you're talking about.

135
00:07:36.831 --> 00:07:39.459
I've lost the thread.
but I'm the butterfly.

136
00:07:39.709 --> 00:07:40.710
Okay.

137
00:07:42.003 --> 00:07:42.837
All right.

138
00:07:45.548 --> 00:07:48.217
What's this over here?
Is this a new listing you're working on?

139
00:07:49.677 --> 00:07:52.054
Yes. That's Sapphire Terrace.

140
00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:55.683
I have exclusive pre-sale rights.
Six units. ocean-facing.

141
00:07:55.766 --> 00:07:57.685
Perfect for a rich bachelor.

142
00:07:58.102 --> 00:07:59.854
Mmm. Really?

143
00:08:00.897 --> 00:08:01.856
Know any?

144
00:08:03.149 --> 00:08:03.983
Yeah.

145
00:08:05.234 --> 00:08:06.235
I think I might.

146
00:08:06.986 --> 00:08:10.364
I've just been working here for
three years and I still get the minimum.

147
00:08:10.448 --> 00:08:13.576
You know. when we hired you.
you were like.

148
00:08:13.659 --> 00:08:16.287
"Pay me what you want. Angela.
I just wanna help. Angela."

149
00:08:16.370 --> 00:08:18.331
Just give her a raise.

150
00:08:18.414 --> 00:08:20.208
Abe. I got this. thank you.

151
00:08:20.875 --> 00:08:23.294
It's just that I live with my family now.

152
00:08:23.377 --> 00:08:25.463
and I would really like
to be able to pitch in.

153
00:08:25.546 --> 00:08:28.799
Just give her what she wants.
or I'll go ape-shit.

154
00:08:29.050 --> 00:08:30.301
- Abe!
<i>- </i>What?

155
00:08:32.428 --> 00:08:33.386
I'll talk to management.

156
00:08:33.471 --> 00:08:35.722
Thank you. Angela.
Thank you. thank you. thank you.

157
00:08:39.477 --> 00:08:41.270
- Hey.
- Judy. I need to talk to you.

158
00:08:41.354 --> 00:08:44.148
There's nothing to talk about.
'cause I'm not pregnant. so don't worry.

159
00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:45.274
It's not that.

160
00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:48.569
A detective came by the gallery today.

161
00:08:48.653 --> 00:08:50.613
started asking me questions
about the Mustang.

162
00:08:50.821 --> 00:08:52.448
- Freaked me out.
- What kind of detective?

163
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:53.574
I don't know. A black one.

164
00:08:53.658 --> 00:08:56.369
Oh! That's the guy I was dating.
That's Nick. We're fine.

165
00:08:56.452 --> 00:08:58.538
How are we fine?
Why were you dating a black detective?

166
00:08:58.621 --> 00:08:59.455
Don't be racist.

167
00:08:59.539 --> 00:09:02.041
- It's not racist to call him black.
- It is when you say it.

168
00:09:02.124 --> 00:09:05.461
He's actually really sweet. He's trying to
help Jen find the hit-and-run driver.

169
00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:07.129
- You're the fucking driver!
- I know!

170
00:09:07.213 --> 00:09:09.590
But I was getting them
off our scent. okay?

171
00:09:09.840 --> 00:09:11.842
And it was the only thing
that was making Jen happy.

172
00:09:11.926 --> 00:09:14.679
Jesus Christ. Judy.
Why don't you just fucking confess?

173
00:09:14.762 --> 00:09:16.472
- You clearly wanna get caught!
- No. I don't.

174
00:09:16.556 --> 00:09:19.183
She can't find out. I can't lose her
and I can't lose those kids.

175
00:09:19.642 --> 00:09:21.143
- I'm gonna fix it.
- You're gonna fix it?

176
00:09:21.227 --> 00:09:22.520
- Yes.
- 'Cause you're a mastermind?

177
00:09:22.603 --> 00:09:23.854
Yes. I'm gonna call Nick.

178
00:09:23.938 --> 00:09:25.815
And say what?
He asked if you own the Mustang.

179
00:09:26.482 --> 00:09:27.817
- He did?
- Yes!

180
00:09:27.900 --> 00:09:30.111
He's on to us
'cause you fucking led him there.

181
00:09:30.236 --> 00:09:31.946
I told you to listen to me
and you couldn't.

182
00:09:32.029 --> 00:09:33.406
could you. fucking bleeding heart.

183
00:09:33.739 --> 00:09:35.616
God damn it.
You have no idea how to work people.

184
00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:37.868
I'm sorry
I'm not as good a criminal as you!

185
00:09:37.994 --> 00:09:40.079
- Hey. Hey!
- Ow!

186
00:09:40.162 --> 00:09:41.289
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

187
00:09:41.872 --> 00:09:44.333
You listen to me.
Let me get one thing straight here. okay?

188
00:09:44.917 --> 00:09:47.378
If anybody goes down for this. it is you.
You were driving.

189
00:09:48.296 --> 00:09:50.715
You are the criminal.
I'm the only eyewitness.

190
00:09:51.757 --> 00:09:54.760
- But you said we were in this together.
- Well. now it's every man for himself.

191
00:09:54.844 --> 00:09:55.886
[cell phone buzzes]

192
00:09:56.262 --> 00:09:58.306
And look. it's your friend calling me.

193
00:09:58.889 --> 00:10:00.808
- Why is Jen calling you?
- Jen. what's going on?

194
00:10:11.777 --> 00:10:14.655
You killed that nice lady's husband.
didn't you?

195
00:10:21.912 --> 00:10:22.788
It's okay.

196
00:10:26.208 --> 00:10:27.043
It's okay.

197
00:10:32.548 --> 00:10:35.051
But don't let that asshole
push you around.

198
00:10:36.594 --> 00:10:37.970
I don't know what to do.

199
00:10:39.013 --> 00:10:40.264
What do you wanna do?

200
00:10:42.058 --> 00:10:43.434
I wanna tell the truth.

201
00:10:44.894 --> 00:10:45.936
Well...

202
00:10:47.146 --> 00:10:49.857
they say the truth shall set you free.

203
00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:55.488
I'm telling you. Judy Hale and Steve Wood

204
00:10:55.571 --> 00:10:57.365
are responsible
for the Harding hit-and-run.

205
00:10:57.448 --> 00:11:00.201
Okay. But do you have any evidence
that isn't entirely circumstantial?

206
00:11:00.618 --> 00:11:05.456
His gallery. TKG Arts.
is the registered owner of a '66 Mustang.

207
00:11:05.831 --> 00:11:07.958
And whose art does he sell? Judy Hale's.

208
00:11:08.042 --> 00:11:11.462
Okay. Mr. Prager. that's interesting. but
I can't arrest people on coincidence.

209
00:11:11.545 --> 00:11:14.256
They were engaged. They were in cahoots.

210
00:11:14.340 --> 00:11:16.092
Cahoots is not
a chargeable offense either.

211
00:11:17.009 --> 00:11:19.762
They broke up a few weeks after the crime.

212
00:11:19.845 --> 00:11:22.390
Guess what could ruin a relationship?
Fucking killing a guy could.

213
00:11:22.473 --> 00:11:25.017
- Right.
- Then she moves in with Jen Harding?

214
00:11:25.101 --> 00:11:26.185
The widow?

215
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:29.021
They did it. I know it in my bones.

216
00:11:29.939 --> 00:11:30.815
[sighs]

217
00:11:30.898 --> 00:11:34.860
Mr. Prager. you were romantically involved
with Ms. Hale. correct?

218
00:11:35.361 --> 00:11:37.655
- I was. but...
- I'm assuming that didn't work out.

219
00:11:38.322 --> 00:11:39.156
No.

220
00:11:39.240 --> 00:11:41.867
And you were a detective
for the Santa Ana PD. is that right?

221
00:11:41.951 --> 00:11:42.910
- Yes.
- And yet

222
00:11:42.993 --> 00:11:45.204
you haven't reported to work
in three months. Why is that?

223
00:11:45.871 --> 00:11:46.914
Because I took a...

224
00:11:47.623 --> 00:11:50.376
You know. none of this is relevant.
by the way.

225
00:11:53.129 --> 00:11:55.381
- I took a leave of absence.
- Was it voluntary?

226
00:11:55.589 --> 00:11:57.842
- [scoffs] Who cares?
- What was the nature of the leave?

227
00:12:02.096 --> 00:12:03.180
Psychiatric.

228
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:04.473
Thank you.

229
00:12:06.475 --> 00:12:10.354
Now. I appreciate the tip.
but I have work to do.

230
00:12:16.944 --> 00:12:18.529
Well. thanks for meeting me here.

231
00:12:18.612 --> 00:12:20.823
- Yup. Nice place.
- Yeah.

232
00:12:21.031 --> 00:12:23.159
You know. Jen. when you called.
I got to be honest.

233
00:12:23.492 --> 00:12:24.702
I got a little nervous.

234
00:12:24.785 --> 00:12:27.413
Nervous. huh? Do I make you nervous?

235
00:12:27.496 --> 00:12:30.124
No. no. It's just that everything
that went down with Judy.

236
00:12:30.207 --> 00:12:33.461
and I'm not sure what she told you.
but. you know. I was surprised.

237
00:12:33.544 --> 00:12:34.378
Mm-hm.

238
00:12:34.962 --> 00:12:37.423
- Girl code. I know it's a thing.
- Not really.

239
00:12:37.506 --> 00:12:40.384
I don't wanna talk about Judy right now.
I wanna talk about you.

240
00:12:40.801 --> 00:12:41.969
- Okay.
- And I wanna talk about

241
00:12:42.052 --> 00:12:46.098
what I wanna do for you.
Well. I mean. for us. really.

242
00:12:47.558 --> 00:12:48.934
- Really?
- Yeah.

243
00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:50.603
[exhales]

244
